If \(n\) is a positive integer, one can show that \(\frac{d}{dx}(\sin^n{x}\cos{nx})=n\sin^{n-1}{x}\cos(n+1)x\) (by the appropriate differentiation rules and the trigonometric identity for \(\cos(\alpha + \beta)\) ). $BR
